 is internal to the tradition. These approaches to the commentarial text complicate presuppositions upon which questions of Islam's intellectual decline are erected. As such, Ahmed offers a unique and powerful opportunity to understand the transmission of knowledge across the Islamic world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aIntellectual lifexReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aIslamic philosophyzSouth Asia. 0aLogicvEarly works to 1800. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520975767zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520975767zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520975767/original  a978-3-11-076649-3 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA